title: Wildlife Linkage
name: Wildlife Linkage
description:
Areas of federal, state, private, or mixed land that may not provide good habitat, but are generally safe for wildlife dispersal from one core habitat to another.  In other words, a
given species may not choose to live in a dispersal linkage for even a short period of time, but they would cross the area freely.  Such dispersal linkages are thus important for genetic exchange.  With road closures and restoration, a dispersal linkage may become a wildlife movement linkage.
